replies.body:
I would recommend getting good with supports that have plenty of utility, but you can play what ever like.

Utility: {{champion:412}} {{champion:117}} {{champion:267}} {{champion:43}}{{champion:25}} {{champion:40}} 

Engage with hard CC: {{champion:12}} {{champion:1}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:89}} These tend become almost useless if they get behind just becoming CC bots that will get blown up.

I can think of two that fall somewhere between those types of supports {{champion:53}} {{champion:201}} 

Braum is naturally tanky with a CC, buffs who he jumps to.. Blitz is tanky, but if the team can't delete who ever he pulls then Blitz is pretty useless if the fight doesn't last long enough for his cds.  

Some people will find {{champion:37}} {{champion:16}} frustrating to lane against. The trick is for Sona wait for her to Q then you can trade with her or poke the adc. She will run out of mana or hp and that point she is useless. For Raka you have to all in her before the adc, make sure to dodge her Q so she will have low hp and an easy kill.

Odd ball supports that I like: {{champion:57}} {{champion:79}} 

Once you have found the ones you enjoy playing, play them a ton and master them.

One little tip, once you buy sightstone switch to the sweeper trinket.
